reviewText: This movie shows that Clint Walker is a very good actor.  It takes his talents beyond the Western genre into the depiction of a man hurt by the problems in his life.  His portrayal of Jack Rutherford is sensitive and totally believable.  I enjoyed the movie very much.  The story was interesting.

reviewText: I have been a Clint Walker admirer for many years and of course we always associate him with Cheyenne and that is a roll we will never stray from.  This performance was his best and not surprisingly his attitudes still prevail. The honesty, tenderness  compassion supposedly taught him from the Cheyenne training is present in this role although we see a more mature attitude. Worth buying and I will watch it many times. I have all his series that are out there but one wonders why the power of money people have so ignored his talent. My husband laughed at my crush on Clint Walker...of course we were 1500 miles apart but he is #1 in my book. I anxiously await the other films I have ordered. great viewing!
